OL,3,CCourt rejects bid by mum to be
OL,4,Cconsulted over her daughter's care
OL,6,FHer mum, a former A&E nurse, said
OL,7,Fbecause the wrong box was ticked on
OL,8,Fthe prescription she was asked to
OL,9,Fprove her daughter was disabled, and
OL,10,Fto ask Ruby to sign a letter giving
OL,11,Fher permission to respond for her.
OL,13,FThe months of stress trying to get the
OL,14,FNHS to listen to her prompted Alison
OL,15,Fto get a loan for almost #5,000 to
OL,16,Fapply for Court of Protection
OL,17,FDeputyship to ensure she still has a
OL,18,Fsay over Ruby's complex health needs
OL,19,Fand welfare.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/11
